text:
@MakuchMatthew @mrabetria @drolet_melissa When revealing a rate, you are using partitive division... trying to find out how much of one quantity is in one part (or group) of another. 

Quotative division would be the opposite: trying to find how many groups you can make with a certain amount in each group (the rate)
